Package pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConsistencyPredicateAnnotationProcessor
    Checks that all consistency predicates receive no parameters, return a primitive boolean value, and are public, protected, or private.
    ConsistencyPredicatesConfig  
    ConsistencyPredicateSupport  
    ConsistencyPredicateSystem
    This class contains the old JVSTM code to determine which consistency predicates affect which domain classes.
    DomainConsistencyPredicate
    A DomainConsistencyPredicate is the persistent domain entity that represents a consistency predicate method inside a domain class.
    DomainConsistencyPredicate_Base  
    DomainDependenceRecord
    A DomainDependenceRecord represents the result of the execution of a consistency predicate method for a dependent domain object.
    DomainDependenceRecord_Base  
    Externalization  
    FinalConsistencyPredicate
    A FinalConsistencyPredicate is a PublicConsistencyPredicate that represents a predicate method that is either public or protected, and is final.
    FinalConsistencyPredicate_Base  
    PrivateConsistencyPredicate
    A PrivateConsistencyPredicate is a DomainConsistencyPredicate that represents a predicate method that is private.
    PrivateConsistencyPredicate_Base  
    PublicConsistencyPredicate
    A PublicConsistencyPredicate is a DomainConsistencyPredicate that represents a predicate method that is either public or protected.
    PublicConsistencyPredicate_Base  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ConsistencyPredicate
    Annotates a method inside a domain class, and declares it as a consistency predicate.
